---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About - Coding with Eric">
	<main>
		<h1>About <span class="text-gradient">Eric</span></h1>
		<div class="content">
			<p>
				Hello! I'm Eric, a passionate coding educator dedicated to teaching Python programming
				to children. With years of experience in both programming and education, I've developed
				a unique teaching approach that makes coding fun and accessible for young minds.
			</p>
			
			<h2>Teaching Philosophy</h2>
			<p>
				I believe that every child can learn to code. My teaching methodology focuses on:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Hands-on learning through interactive projects</li>
				<li>Building confidence through achievable challenges</li>
				<li>Fostering creativity and problem-solving skills</li>
				<li>Creating a supportive and engaging learning environment</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Experience</h2>
			<p>
				With years of experience teaching Python, I've inspired countless children to unlock their 
				creativity through coding. My courses are tailored to each child's unique learning pace, 
				making programming not just a skill but a fun and empowering journey toward becoming 
				confident problem-solvers.
			</p>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	main {
		margin: auto;
		padding: 1rem;
		width: 800px;
		max-width: calc(100% - 2rem);
		color: white;
		font-size: 20px;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
	h1 {
		font-size: 3rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1;
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 1em;
	}
	.text-gradient {
		background-image: var(--accent-gradient);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-size: 400%;
		background-position: 0%;
	}
	.content {
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
		padding: 2rem;
		border-radius: 8px;
	}
	h2 {
		color: rgb(var(--accent-light));
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}
	ul {
		margin-left: 2rem;
	}
</style>